messageBody:
Hi. My test parameterized class keeps throwing up this exception, and I can't figure out how to fix it. Could someone point out where my problem lies?

java.lang.IllegalAgumentException: wrong number of arguments
at java.lang.reflect.Constructor.newInstance(Unknown Source)

Here's the parameter method:

@Parameters
public static Collection<Object[]> licenseBaselines() {
ArrayList<Object[]> tests = new ArrayList<Object[]>();
try {
BufferedReader in = new BufferedReader(new FileReader(testFile));
String line;
while((line = in.readLine()) != null)
tests.add(line.split("::"));
in.close();
} catch(Exception e) {
System.out.println("Exception: " + e.toString());
}
return tests;
}
